chh.math.sets

Class OrderedPairAlternate

  • java.lang.Object
    • chh.math.sets.Set
      • chh.math.sets.Pair
        • chh.math.sets.OrderedPairAlternate
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    OrderedTriple

    public class OrderedPairAlternate
extends Pair
    An OrderedPairAlternate is a set that encodes the order of its two components. The order of these elements is relevant; that is, (new OrderedPairAlternate(a,b)).equals(new OrderedPairAlternate(b,a)) returns false, while (new Pair(a,b)).equals(new Pair(b,a))==true.
    An OrderedPairAlternate is similar to a Tuple with 2 components (a 2-tuple), however they are structurally different from a set-theoretic approach.
    new OrderedPairAlternate(a,b) is defined by ... recursively by super(new Tuple(a,b,c,d,...,y), z), where the basis new Tuple() is defined by super(new EmptySet()).

    2013.07.26
